      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The ethical defense rests on the principle of reciprocity and the social contract; a society has a moral obligation to its existing citizens, whose rights and resources are established within that nation's framework. Allowing unchecked entry fundamentally violates the contract that underpins a stable society, creating an unsustainable burden on those who abide by the established laws. Therefore, enforcing borders is not an act of malice, but a necessary act of responsible stewardship over the shared resources and legal integrity of the nation.",
      "source": "target",
